        {
          "id": "patient_rights_poster",
          "title": "Patient Rights 101",
          "type": "computer",
          "x": 3,
          "y": 3,
          "fact": "Under HIPAA, patients aren't just bodies in beds—they have actual power. The Big 5 Patient Rights: (1) Right to Access Their Records within 30 days, (2) Right to Request Amendments to incorrect info, (3) Right to an Accounting of Disclosures for the last 6 years, (4) Right to Request Restrictions on who sees their info, (5) Right to Confidential Communications. Bottom line: Patients own their health data. We're just the janitors managing it."
        }
      ],
      "spawnPoint": {"x": 10, "y": 12}
