        {
          "id": "security_training",
          "title": "When You CAN Share PHI (Without Going to Jail)",
          "type": "whiteboard",
          "x": 17,
          "y": 10,
          "fact": "HIPAA isn't trying to STOP healthcare—it just wants you to be thoughtful. You can share PHI without patient authorization for: Treatment, Payment, Operations (TPO - The Holy Trinity), Required by Law (court orders, mandatory reporting), Public Health (disease outbreaks), Law Enforcement (with a warrant), Deceased Persons (coroners, funeral directors), and Emergencies. The Catch: Even when permitted, still use MINIMUM NECESSARY."
        }
      ],
      "spawnPoint": {"x": 10, "y": 12}
