        {
          "id": "when_to_say_no",
          "title": "The Art of the HIPAA Shutdown",
          "type": "poster",
          "x": 16,
          "y": 3,
          "fact": "Not everyone who asks for PHI gets it. Sometimes your job is to be the bouncer at Club Medical Records. Automatic NO Situations: Family Members Without Authorization, Employers asking for diagnosis (they get work notes only), Marketing Without Authorization, Anyone Via Unsecured Communication (no texting lab results!). The Script: 'I'm unable to confirm or deny any patient information without proper authorization.' Saying no to inappropriate requests is literally your job."
        }
      ],
      "spawnPoint": {"x": 10, "y": 12}
